author: jpieper
msg: Issue #1551: 'svn log' handles unversioned targets poorly
Since the log subcommand cannot properly support multiple WC targets
currently, there is no reason why it should not error out when passed
an unversioned WC path.  When log is fixed to handle multiple WC
targets, this can be revisited.
* subversion/libsvn_client/log.c
(svn_client_log2): Return an unversioned resource error if the sole
WC target passed is not found in the entries file.

author: jpieper
msg: Fix some subversion style issues and an array indexing bug introduced
in r11599 noticed by Philip Martin <philip@codematters.co.uk>.
* subversion/clients/log-cmd.c
(svn_cl__log): Put braces where they need to be, don't retrieve the
first element of the targets list more than it needs to be, and
actually loop through the target list instead of only checking the
second element over and over again.
